---
description: Keep route files thin and boundary-focused
globs: app/routes/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Route Boundary Rules

- Treat routes as transport layers (HTTP in/out, auth checks, redirects, error mapping).
- For app proxy and webhook routes, verify Shopify trust first, then delegate.
- Prefer calling tRPC callers or services; avoid embedding domain logic in routes.
- Never call `db.*` directly from route files.
- For webhook failures, log and return non-2xx so retries can happen.
